A serene Chinese monastery garden in Studio Ghibli style, featuring a collection of whimsical stone statues resembling traditional Chinese folk figures scattered among lush moss-covered rocks and twisted bonsai pines. The statues have round, cheerful faces with exaggerated expressions of joy and contemplation, some meditating, others playfully posed. Soft afternoon light filters through weeping willow branches, casting dappled shadows across weathered stone pathways. A small koi pond reflects the warm amber and sage green tones of the garden. The scene blends Eastern spirituality with childlike wonder, rendered in Ghibli's signature painterly watercolor aesthetic with gentle gradients and dreamy atmospheric perspective.
